y delivered radios to the us army  this effort will provide “a tenfold increase in satcom capacity for secure overthehorizon military communications” according to chris marzilli president of general dynamics c system in a recent press release general dynamics c systems truly excels in the area of innovation   its two new encryptors in the protecdr product family were recently certified by the national security agency nsa for securing information at the top secret level and below the organization also recently completed critical ground system modifications and technology updates to support nasa’s three nextgeneration tracking and data relay satellites tdrs in addition the general dynamics’ sponsored edge innovation network officially opened its new space innovation center which will connect nasa and other government agency professionals with more than  industry and academia members with a continued focus on providing the most innovative solutions to the government defense and public safety arenas – while also securing significant contract wins — we are proud to announce that general dynamics c systems is officially this week’s winning contractor” stay tuned for more posts about contractors proving to be nimble in the face of challenging times in our new “winning contractor” series   market connections inc  all rights reserved privacy policy mobile menu problems we solvelatest research  infographicsclient worktoolsbest practices  howtoblogabout us▼servicescase studiescertificationsgovernment contractsfaqscareerscontact usteamnews  events▼in the newsupcoming eventspast eventspress releasespodcastsvideoswebinarsnewsletterscontact us chris marzilli general dynamics mission systems president chosen to wash00 for communications tech leadership  govcon exec browse home  0  february    chris marzilli general dynamics mission systems president chosen to wash00 for communications tech leadership july   govcon exec privatepublic connections for contract leadership posts from go